<p>Thousands of people gathered in Manila on Sunday in a mass rally organised by the Iglesia ni Cristo to demand accountability over a widening corruption scandal involving flood-control projects, which reports say saw billions of pesos spent on substandard work and alleged kickbacks from construction companies that implicated members of Congress and top officials. The demonstrations have intensified public scrutiny and added political pressure on President Ferdinand Marcos Jr. as investigations and calls for answers grow.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/2cmqSCt7M1Uyklg4zCmFq3K55y9P1yK7EqxIzdBpIbTfO44JGq1uP2QUwPVK_trMa_j9HdLA4xhqg_GxCADObPenmI_KJGIsFHOX4AE7GEoUo5UOPkipEDrd_Q8VDTwWZgogAccoK-bBVDM8rIJLbYtswG1a2pj1PYuKiiYR8-ECRHJ5jQA' alt='Iglesia ni Cristo members gather at Quirino Grandstand during the rally in Manila' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Assembly details: Members of Iglesia ni Cristo, many wearing white shirts, assembled at the historic Quirino Grandstand and nearby streets for the gathering, with some participants camping overnight ahead of programmes later in the day.</li><li>Crowd estimate: Police reported a crowd estimate of about 14,500 by 8am local time during the morning of the rally, illustrating variance in crowd counts across reports.</li><li>Event duration: Organisers launched the action as a planned three-day rally in Manila to press for accountability and investigations into the flood-control projects.</li><li>Allegations focus: Reporting highlights that the scandal centers on flood-control works where contractors allegedly avoided accountability while public funds were spent on substandard projects, described in media coverage as involving billions of pesos.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Iglesia ni Cristo (organisers / participants): Members of the church gathered to call for accountability from public officials over the alleged corruption in flood-control projects, using their assembly to press for investigations and transparency. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/3332976/philippine-church-rallies-over-corruption-scandal-pressure-mounts-macros'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Philippine police: Police provided an on-site estimate of roughly 14,500 people at the rally by 8am local time, reflecting official crowd counts used for operational planning. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/3332976/philippine-church-rallies-over-corruption-scandal-pressure-mounts-macros'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Investigative reporting / press: Journalists reporting on the story said construction companies are accused of paying large kickbacks to influential politicians and officials to win contracts and avoid scrutiny of anomalies in projects. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/tens-of-thousands-rally-in-manila-over-corruption-scandal-that-implicates-top-philippine-officials/article70286621.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/tens-of-thousands-rally-in-manila-over-corruption-scandal-that-implicates-top-philippine-officials/article70286621.ece'>Tens of thousands rally in Manila over corruption scandal that implicates top Philippine officials</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/southeast-asia/article/3332976/philippine-church-rallies-over-corruption-scandal-pressure-mounts-macros'>Philippine church rallies over corruption scandal, piling pressure on Marcos</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/16/enormous-evil-thousands-rally-in-the-philippines-over-corruption-scandal'>‘Enormous evil’: Thousands rally in the Philippines over corruption scandal</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/thousands-rally-in-manila-over-corruption-scandal-that-implicated-top-philippine-officials-13951105.html'>Thousands rally in Manila over corruption scandal that implicate